EU changes rules to get visas
People should visit Visa Requesters Service centres before their interview in the Consular Section; the cost will be lower and as well as the waiting time.
With effect from 10 January 2011, the procedure for processing a visa will be changed at the United States Embassy and consulates.
With the new procedure, most applicants should visit Visa Requesters Service Centres (ACS) before their interview in the Consular Section.
The ASC staff will receive biometric information from the applicant, which will be reviewed by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will have certain advantages for applicants, including:
The total cost of processing the visa will be lower, no longer will be necessary to make a payment to conclude the date, another payment to process the visa application and more so that the mail service will deliver the document.
The vacuum cleaner will only make a single payment covering the three services.
The current rate will remain unchanged: $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for a requested visa (including visas for temporary workers) and $390 for commercial and investment visas.
People who wish to renew their visa will not have to go to an interview with the Consular Officer, but they will only go to the nearest ASC where they will present their documents and take their marks.
Because biometric information will be taken into the ASC, applicants who will need a second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain in this less time than in the past.
Similarly, those who apply for visas in Consulates in Juárez, Monterrey and New Laredo will no longer pay the extra fee of $26.
For further information on the new visa application procedure, please visit the following page: http://mexico.usebassy.gov/bolettines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
